Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Sprinkle with half the @Central
American Style Spice Mix{1/2%sachet}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer. TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%mins}. Turn
halfway through.

Meanwhile, remove the @Slow Cooked British Pork{425%g} shoulder from the
packaging.

Place in an #ovenproof dish{} along with the juices. Season with salt and pepper
and cover loosely with #foil{}.

Roast on the middle shelf for ~{25-30%mins}. IMPORTANT: Ensure the pork is
piping hot throughout.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and slice the @red onion{1/2}(halved, peeled and sliced
thinly).

Pop it into a #small bowl{} and add half the @Red Wine Vinegar{12%ml} and @Sugar
for Pickling{1%tsp}. Add a pinch of salt, mix together and set aside to pickle.

Pour the remaining @Red Wine Vinegar{12%ml} into a #medium bowl{}. Add the
@Sugar for the Dressing{1/2%tsp} and @Olive Oil for the Dressing{1%tbsp} and
season with salt and pepper. Mix to combine, then set aside.

Drain the @Sweetcorn{160%g} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the sweetcorn and cook until charred, ~{5-6%mins}. Adjust the heat
if necessary. Stir only twice during this time - you want the sweetcorn to pick
up some nice colour.

Stir through the remaining @Central American Style Spice Mix{1/2%sachet} and fry
for ~{1%min}.

Transfer the charred corn to the bowl of dressing. Add the
@Coleslaw Mix{120%g}, then toss to combine and set aside.

Once the pork is cooked, remove from the oven, then discard the foil and any
cooking juices. Use two #forks{} to gently break apart the pork.

Stir through the @Chipotle Paste{40%g}, @BBQ Sauce{48%g} and @Water{1%tbsp}.
Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Return the pork to the oven to bake until sticky, ~{5%mins}.

Meanwhile, halve the @Burger Buns{2}. Pop into the oven to warm through,
~{2-3%mins}.

When everything's ready, spread the @Mayonnaise{2%tbsp} over the bun lids. Top
the bases with the shredded pork and half the pickled onion, then sandwich
shut with the bun lids.

Toss the remaining pickled onion through the slaw.

Serve the buns with the chips and charred corn slaw on the side.

Enjoy!